iego lives in the high desert of central México where he walks the cities and mountains, plays drums with jazz combos and in musical / poetry collaborations, writes, and studies. His work appears in various journals and on public radio. His web site is victordavid.com.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''>---<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''>Again, many thanks and best to Sugared Water with your launch.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''>Sincerely,<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''>Victor David <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><b><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif"''>From:</span></b><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif"''> sugaredwaterlit=gmail.com@email.submittable.com [mailto:sugaredwaterlit=gmail.com@email.submittable.com] <b>On Behalf Of </b>Sugared Water<br><b>Sent:</b> Friday, July 05, 2013 1:46 PM<br><b>To:</b> Victor David Sandiego<br><b>Subject:</b> RE: [Sugared Water] moonlight crossing the yard and climbing over the hedges<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Dear Victor David Sandiego, <br><br>Thank you for sending us &quot;moonlight crossing the yard and climbing over the hedges.&quot; We love &quot;Advice from my father&quot; and would like to publish it in the upcoming issue of Sugared Water! <br><br>Please respond to confirm that this work is still available to us either by using the &quot;add note&quot; feature on your submissions panel, or by emailing sugaredwaterlit@gmail.com. <br><br>Best, <br>Nicci Mechler <br>Sugared Water <br><span style=''border:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0in''><img width=100 height=100 id="Picture_x0020_1" src="cid:~WRD000.jpg" alt="Description: Image removed by sender."></span><o:p></o:p></p></div></body></html>');
