ult\r\n\t{mso-style-type:export-only;\r\n\tfont-size:10.0pt;\r\n\tfont-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";}\r\n@page WordSection1\r\n\t{size:8.5in 11.0in;\r\n\tmargin:1.0in 1.0in 1.0in 1.0in;}\r\ndiv.WordSection1\r\n\t{page:WordSection1;}\r\n--></style><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<o:shapedefaults v:ext="edit" spidmax="1026" />\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<o:shapelayout v:ext="edit">\r\n<o:idmap v:ext="edit" data="1" />\r\n</o:shapelayout></xml><![endif]--></head><body lang=EN-US link=blue vlink=purple><div class=WordSection1><p class=MsoPlainText>Hello  Ms. McQuerry<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText>I''m entering the Missouri Review Audio Poetry contest with two poems from a longer work titled The Red Sky Inside Me. The total time for these two poems is 8:06.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText>Because of email concerns, I am breaking my entry up into two emails. This email is Part Two which has the second mp3 file. I&#8217;m also attaching the application form even though it&#8217;s a duplicate of the first email.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText>Per your guidelines, here''s a brief program synopsis and bio.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText>---<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText>These recordings are of two poems from a longer work titled The Red Sky Inside Me. The two poems are: The first death of God, and Only when gods arrive covered in red dust will we recognize their child faces. Everything written and produced by Victor David Sandiego. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText>Victor David Sandiego was the winner of the 1st WordStorm Poetry Competition held on Vancouver Island in British Columbia, a winner of the Jeanne Lohmann Poetry Prize, and the winner of the 2009 Crab Creek Review poetry contest. His work appears in various journals and on public radio. He lives in the high desert of central México.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText>---<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText>Thank you. I would appreciate that you acknowledge receipt of this email.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText>Victor David Sandiego<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText>Missouri Review Audio Poetry -PART 2 of 2<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText>attached:<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText>Sandiego_2PoemsFromTheRedSkyInsideMe_AppForm.pdf<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoPlainText>Sandiego_2PoemsFromTheRedSkyInsideMe_Part2.mp3<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p></div></body></html>');
INSERT INTO "submission_message" ("id", "entry_id", "submissionbatchid", "outgoing", "sender_name", "sender_email", "recipient_name", "recipient_email", "subject", "display", "sent_date", "received_date", "body_format", "body") VALUES (79, E'00000000FC0A50B868F35745AE9D2EED70629592C4022000', 177, E'0', E'info@arvonfoundation.org', E'info@arvonfoundation.org', E'99poets@victordavidsandiego.com', E'99poets@victordavidsandiego.com', E'Poetry Competition', E'Poetry Competition', '2010-08-16 09:17:11', '2010-08-16 09:48:35', 1, E'Dear Victor David Sandiego,\r\n\r\nThank you for submitting your poetry to the 2010 Arvon International Poetry Competition. This email is confirmation that your entry has been received.\r\n\r\n7882 - The eyes of San Cristóbal\r\n7888 - The first son of Muwadi\r\n7896 - AVENUES of SAINTS\r\n7899 - The undercover faithful\r\n7902 - I should love tomorrow\r\n\r\nYou can view the poems you have submitted, or enter more poems, by logging into Your Account (http://arvonfoundation.org/). A log in box can be found on the left hand side of the Arvon website. Please note, any poems that have not been paid for will not be entered into the competition.\r\n\r\nPrize winners will be informed by 1 October 2010. Unfortunately, Arvon is unable to contact or give feedback to those who have not won a prize. A full list of the prize winners will be published on the Arvon website on 5 November 2010. Sign up for Arvon''s monthly e-newsletter (http://arvonfoundation.org/index2.php\x3fpid=107&email=&x=177&y=13) to hear when the results are announced and stay up to date with news from Arvon.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime, you can pre-order your copy of the competition anthology, containing all the prize-winning and commended poems, by following this link (http://arvonfoundation.org/p237.html).\r\n\r\nGood luck!\r\n\r\nThe Arvon Foundation');
INSERT INTO "submission_message" ("id", "entry_id", "submissionbatchid", "outgoing", "sender_name", "sender_email", "recipient_name", "recipient_email", "subject", "display", "sent_date", "received_date", "body_format", "body") VALUES (80, E'00000000FC0A50B868F35745AE9D2EED70629592C4082000', 243, E'0', E'uspoetsinmexico@verizon.net', E'uspoetsinmexico@verizon.net', E'uspoetsinmexico@verizon.net', E'uspoetsinmexico@verizon.net', E'Entry Received', E'Entry Received', '2012-09-03 19:29:35', '2012-09-03 19:29:40', 2, E'<div style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial; COLOR: #000000; FONT-SIZE: 12px"><div>Hello, Thank you for entering the 2013 Merida Fellowship Award competition to be judged by Kimiko Hahn.&nbsp; <br /><br />The recipient will be announced by email to all entrants first, and then on Facebook and our website on September 30, 2012.<br /><br /><br /></div><span><br />U.S. Poets in Mexico<br />P.O. Box 4150<br />Grand Central Station<br />New York, NY 10163<br /><a class="parsedLink" href="http://www.uspoetsinmexico.org" target="_blank">http://www.uspoetsinmexico.org</a></span></div>');
INSERT INTO "submission_message" ("id", "entry_id", "submissionbatchid", "outgoing", "sender_name", "sender_email", "recipient_name", "recipient_email", "subject", "display", "sent_date", "received_date", "body_format", "body") VALUES (81, E'00000000FC0A50B868F35745AE9D2EED70629592E4152000', 269, E'1', E'Victor David Sandiego', E'99poets@VictorDavid.com', E'''denovo@crpress.org''', E'denovo@crpress.org', E'FW: De Novo manuscript submission: The First Book of Muwadi', E'FW: De Novo manuscript submission: The First Book of Muwadi', '2013-07-13 19:08:15', '2013-07-13 19:08:00', 2, E'<html xmlns:v="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml" xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" xmlns:w="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word" xmlns:m="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/2004/12/omml" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40"><head><meta name=Generator content="Microsoft Word 14 (filtered medium)"><style><!--\r\n/* Font Definitions */\r\n@font-face\r\n\t{font-family:Calibri;\r\n\tpanose-1:2 15 5 2 2 2 4 3 2 4;}\r\n@font-face\r\n\t{font-family:Tahoma;\r\n\tpanose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;}\r\n@font-face\r\n\t{font-family:Verdana;\r\n\tpanose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;}\r\n/* Style Definitions */\r\np.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\r\n\t{margin:0in;\r\n\tmargin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n\tfont-size:11.0pt;\r\n\tfont-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";}\r\na:link, span.MsoHyperlink\r\n\t{mso-style-priority:99;\r\n\tcolor:blue;\r\n\ttext-decoration:underline;}\r\na:visited, span.MsoHyperlinkFollowed\r\n\t{mso-style-priority:99;\r\n\tcolor:purple;\r\n\ttext-decoration:underline;}\r\np.MsoPlainText, li.MsoPlainText, div.MsoPlainText\r\n\t{mso-style-priority:99;\r\n\tmso-style-link:"Plain Text Char";\r\n\tmargin:0in;\r\n\tmargin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n\tfont-size:11.0pt;\r\n\tfont-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";}\r\nspan.PlainTextChar\r\n\t{mso-style-name:"Plain Text Char";\r\n\tmso-style-priority:99;\r\n\tmso-style-link:"Plain Text";\r\n\tfont-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";}\r\np.Indented, li.Indented, div.Indented\r\n\t{mso-style-name:Indented;\r\n\tmso-style-priority:7;\r\n\tmargin-top:0in;\r\n\tmargin-right:0in;\r\n\tmargin-bottom:0in;\r\n\tmargin-left:9.0pt;\r\n\tmargin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n\tfont-size:10.0pt;\r\n\tfont-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";}\r\nspan.EmailStyle20\r\n\t{mso-style-type:personal;\r\n\tfont-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";\r\n\tcolor:black;}\r\nspan.EmailStyle21\r\n\t{mso-style-type:personal;}\r\nspan.EmailStyle22\r\n\t{mso-style-type:personal-reply;\r\n\tfont-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";\r\n\tcolor:black;}\r\n.MsoChpDefault\r\n\t{mso-style-type:export-only;\r\n\tfont-size:10.0pt;}\r\n@page WordSection1\r\n\t{size:8.5in 11.0in;\r\n\tmargin:1.0in 1.0in 1.0in 1.0in;}\r\ndiv.WordSection1\r\n\t{page:WordSection1;}\r\n--></style><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<o:shapedefaults v:ext="edit" spidmax="1026" />\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<o:shapelayout v:ext="edit">\r\n<o:idmap v:ext="edit" data="1" />\r\n</o:shapelayout></xml><![endif]--></head><body lang=EN-US link=blue vlink=purple><div class=WordSection1><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''>Hello C&amp;R Press<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''>When I emailed you in April to enter the De Novo, I never received an acknowledgement that the manuscript had been received. Now I read on your web site that the De Novo is only for authors you already have a relationship with. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''><a href="http://www.crpress.org/the-denovo-prize/">http://www.crpress.org/the-denovo-prize/</a><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal>&#8220;Open to authors who have published their first or second poetry books with C&amp;R, De Novo Prize winners receive&#8230;&#8221;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Can you please clarify\x3f Is this really true, that you only want more of your existing authors (for De Novo, at least)\x3f <o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Since I don&#8217;t have a book with C&amp;R, did I throw my time and money away\x3f Or is this change for 2014 onwards\x3f<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Did you indeed receive my manuscript at all\x3f<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Thanks. Hope to hear from you soon.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Sincerely,<o:p></o:p></p><div><p class=MsoNormal>Victor David Sandiego<span style=''color:black''><o:p></o:p></span></p></div><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";color:black''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><div><div style=''border:none;border-top:solid #B5C4DF 1.0pt;padding:3.0pt 0in 0in 0in''><p class=MsoNormal><b><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif"''>From:</span></b><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif"''> Victor David Sandiego [mailto:99poets@VictorDavid.com] <br><b>Sent:</b> Monday, April 29, 2013 5:26 PM<br><b>To:</b> ''denovo@crpress.org''<br><b>Subject:</b> De Novo manuscript submission: The First Book of Muwadi<o:p></o:p></span></p></div></div><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>C &amp; R Press<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>2013 De Novo Prize for a 1st or 2nd Book of Poetry<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>April 29, 2013<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Hello C &amp; R Press -<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Since my work falls well outside of the mainstream of current American work, I approach publications where I must pay to be considered quite judiciously. I must say I was happy to read that C &amp; R wants poetry that &#8220;threatens our preconceived notions&#8230;&#8221; &#8211; Sounds good to me; I hope your editorial assistants and guest judge share the sentiment.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>At any rate, C &amp; R seems like a good press, with a good heart. So, with that thought, and in that spirit, I''ve attached a PDF document that contains my manuscript <i>The First Book of Muwadi</i> as entry for the 2013 De Novo Prize. As requested in your guidelines, the manuscript does not contain my name.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Some of the pieces from the manuscript have been published in journals, or are coming soon. However, to preserve anonymity, I&#8217;ve removed the Acknowledgments page from the manuscript.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Also, as requested, a brief bio:<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=Indented>Victor David Sandiego lives in the high desert of central México where he walks the cities and mountains, plays drums with jazz combos and in musical / poetry collaborations, writes, and studies. His work appears in various journals and on public radio. His web site is victordavid.com.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Thanks, and of best of effort to you in sorting through what is likely to be a large quantity of excellent entries. If you need any more information from me, please let me know.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Victor David Sandiego<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><a href="mailto:99Poets@VictorDavid.com">99Poets@VictorDavid.com</a><o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>206.317.1345 (U.S. Skype #)<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Manuscript: The First Book of Muwadi<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Attachments:<o:p></o:p></p><p class=Indented>C&amp;R_Press-The First Book of Muwadi-Victor David Sandiego-Manuscript.pdf<o:p></o:p></p><p class=Indented>C&amp;R_Press-The First Book of Muwadi-Victor David Sandiego-CoverLetter.pdf<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>PayPal transaction number: 1XY62010HC523101P<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p></div></body></html>');
INSERT INTO "submission_message" ("id", "entry_id", "submissionbatchid", "outgoing", "sender_name", "sender_email", "recipient_name", "recipient_email", "subject", "display", "sent_date", "received_date", "body_format", "body") VALUES (82, E'00000000FC0A50B868F35745AE9D2EED7062959224082000', 231, E'0', E'Generations Literary Journal', E'editor@generationslitmag.org', E'Victor David Sandiego', E'vds@victordavid.com', E'Re: Generations Literary Journal: EDITS for How I Arrived Here', E'Re: Generations Literary Journal: EDITS for How I Arrived Here', '2012-07-30 14:21:35', '2012-07-30 14:21:37', 2, E'Thanks Victor.<div>We&#39;ve made the change to the capitalization in your name. </div><div><br></div><div>We will be in touch again shortly.</div><div><br></div><div>All the best, </div><div>Kiala<br><br><div class="gmail_quote">\r\nOn Wed, Jul 18, 2012 at 10:23 AM, Victor David Sandiego <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:vds@victordavid.com" target="_blank">vds@victordavid.com</a>&gt;</span> wrote:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex">\r\n<div lang="EN-US" link="blue" vlink="purple"><div><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#002060">Hello Kiala –<u></u><u></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal">\r\n<span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#002060"><u></u> <u></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#002060">Thanks for the document. The line breaks are fine. Quite a bit of my work is done in paragraph style. I know that it needs to break differently in another layout / page size.<u></u><u></u></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#002060"><u></u> <u></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#002060">However, one important detail, please. My last name. It’s not exactly spelled wrong but the “d” should not be capitalized. Simply “Sandiego”.<u></u><u></u></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#002060"><u></u> <u></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#002060">Thanks again! I’m pleased to find a good home for this! <u></u><u></u></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#002060"><u></u> <u></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#002060">Victor David Sandiego <u></u><u></u></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#002060"><u></u> <u></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#002060"><u></u> <u></u></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Tahoma&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">From:</span></b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Tahoma&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"> <a href="mailto:kiala.givehand@gmail.com" target="_blank">kiala.givehand@gmail.com</a> [mailto:<a href="mailto:kiala.givehand@gmail.com" target="_blank">kiala.givehand@gmail.com</a>] <b>On Behalf Of </b>Generations Literary Journal<br>\r\n<b>Sent:</b> Tuesday, July 17, 2012 6:04 PM<br><b>To:</b> Victor David Sandiego<br><b>Subject:</b> Generations Literary Journal: EDITS for How I Arrived Here<u></u><u></u></span></p><div><div class="h5"><p class="MsoNormal">\r\n<u></u> <u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal">Hi Victor,<br><br>Please review the suggested edits for your piece, [How I Arrived Here]. Mostly, we need you to approve the line breaks. Because of space limitations, your lines cannot be the width of a standard piece of paper, so we&#39;ve adjusted to fit our page size. <br>\r\n<br>If you agree with the edits as they appear in the attached file, please indicate this by replying YES to this email. Your yes reply will confirm that we can move forward with publishing the edited version of your submission. <br>\r\n<br>If you have questions, please reply to this email to keep the thread intact. <br><br>If you disagree with the edits and would rather we did not publish your piece, please let us know that immediately. <u></u><u></u></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"> <u></u><u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal">Please be sure to check the spelling of your name as well. <br><br><b>Please reply by midnight (PST) Friday July 20, 2012. </b><br><br>We look forward to working with you as we continue the process. <br>\r\n<br>All the best, <br>The Editors<u></u><u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"><br clear="all"><br>-- <br>-------------------------------------<br>\r\n<a href="http://www.generationslitmag.org" target="_blank">Generations Literary Journal</a><br><br>Twitter: <a href="http://twitter.com/generationslit" target="_blank">@generationslit</a><br>Visit Our <a href="https://www.facebook.com/GenerationsLitJournal" target="_blank">Facebook</a> Page <u></u><u></u></span></p>\r\n</div></div></div></div></blockquote></div><br><br clear="all"><div><br></div>-- <br>-------------------------------------<br>\r\nKiala Givehand, MFA, Ed.S.<br>Founding Editor, <a href="http://www.generationslitmag.org" target="_blank">Generations Literary Journal</a><br><br>Twitter: <a href="http://twitter.com/generationslit" target="_blank">@generationslit</a><br>\r\nVisit Our <a href="https://www.facebook.com/GenerationsLitJournal" target="_blank">Facebook</a> Page <br><br>\r\n</div>');
INSERT INTO "submission_message" ("id", "entry_id", "submissionbatchid", "outgoing", "sender_name", "sender_email", "recipient_name", "recipient_email", "subject", "display", "sent_date", "received_date", "body_format", "body") VALUES (83, E'00000000FC0A50B868F35745AE9D2EED7062959204162000', 269, E'0', E'chad@crpress.org', E'chad@crpress.org', E'Victor David Sandiego', E'99poets@VictorDavid.com', E'RE: FW: De Novo manuscript submission: The First Book of Muwadi', E'RE: FW: De Novo manuscript submission: The First Book of Muwadi', '2013-07-14 06:13:14', '2013-07-14 06:13:16', 2, E'<html><body><span style="font-family:Verdana; color:#000000; font-size:10pt;"><div>Hey Victor--</div><div><br></div><div>This website is brand new (went live two days ago) and you''re pointing out a significant error in the language on that De Novo page. Wow. Hadn''t noticed that at all. My designer must have edited what I gave her incorrectly. I''ll change that right away. Of course we don''t only publish people we already know. That would be silly, narrow, and unethical anyway.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>We did receive your book, which, as you noted was a little unorthodox, and yet it was still named as a semifinalist. One of twelve. There were six finalists. The winner has not yet been named by the finalist judge.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Hope that helps. Good job and continued well-wishes in finding the right place.</div><div><br></div><div><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Chad Prevost</span></div><div><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Partner</span></div><div><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">C&amp;R Press</span></div><div><a title="www.crpress.org" href="http://www.crpress.org" target="_blank">www.crpress.org</a></div><div><span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">(423) 645-5375</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><br><br></div>\r\n<blockquote id="replyBlockquote" webmail="1" style="border-left: 2px solid blue; margin-left: 8px; padding-left: 8px; font-size:10pt; color:black; font-family:verdana;">\r\n<div id="wmQuoteWrapper">\r\n-------- Original Message --------<br>\r\nSubject: FW: De Novo manuscript submission: The First Book of Muwadi<br>\r\nFrom: "Victor David Sandiego" &lt;<a href="mailto:99poets@VictorDavid.com">99poets@VictorDavid.com</a>&gt;<br>\r\nDate: Sat, July 13, 2013 8:08 pm<br>\r\nTo: &lt;<a href="mailto:denovo@crpress.org">denovo@crpress.org</a>&gt;<br>\r\n<br>\r\nHello C&amp;R Press<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nWhen I emailed you in April to enter the De Novo, I never received an<br>\r\nacknowledgement that the manuscript had been received. Now I read on your<br>\r\nweb site that the De Novo is only for authors you already have a<br>\r\nrelationship with. <br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\n<a href="http://www.crpress.org/the-denovo-prize">http://www.crpress.org/the-denovo-prize</a>/<br>\r\n<br>\r\n"Open to authors who have published their first or second poetry books with<br>\r\nC&amp;R, De Novo Prize winners receive..."<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nCan you please clarify\x3f Is this really true, that you only want more of your<br>\r\nexisting authors (for De Novo, at least)\x3f <br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nSince I don''t have a book with C&amp;R, did I throw my time and money away\x3f Or<br>\r\nis this change for 2014 onwards\x3f<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nDid you indeed receive my manuscript at all\x3f<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nThanks. Hope to hear from you soon.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nSincerely,<br>\r\n<br>\r\nVictor David Sandiego<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nFrom: Victor David Sandiego [<a href="mailto:99poets@VictorDavid.com">mailto:99poets@VictorDavid.com</a>] <br>\r\nSent: Monday, April 29, 2013 5:26 PM<br>\r\nTo: ''<a href="mailto:denovo@crpress.org">denovo@crpress.org</a>''<br>\r\nSubject: De Novo manuscript submission: The First Book of Muwadi<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nC &amp; R Press<br>\r\n<br>\r\n2013 De Novo Prize for a 1st or 2nd Book of Poetry<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nApril 29, 2013<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nHello C &amp; R Press -<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nSince my work falls well outside of the mainstream of current American work,<br>\r\nI approach publications where I must pay to be considered quite judiciously.<br>\r\nI must say I was happy to read that C &amp; R wants poetry that "threatens our<br>\r\npreconceived notions..." - Sounds good to me; I hope your editorial<br>\r\nassistants and guest judge share the sentiment.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nAt any rate, C &amp; R seems like a good press, with a good heart. So, with that<br>\r\nthought, and in that spirit, I''ve attached a PDF document that contains my<br>\r\nmanuscript The First Book of Muwadi as entry for the 2013 De Novo Prize. As<br>\r\nrequested in your guidelines, the manuscript does not contain my name.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nSome of the pieces from the manuscript have been published in journals, or<br>\r\nare coming soon. However, to preserve anonymity, I''ve removed the<br>\r\nAcknowledgments page from the manuscript.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nAlso, as requested, a brief bio:<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nVictor David Sandiego lives in the high desert of central México where he<br>\r\nwalks the cities and mountains, plays drums with jazz combos and in musical<br>\r\n/ poetry collaborations, writes, and studies. His work appears in various<br>\r\njournals and on public radio. His web site is <a href="http://victordavid.com">victordavid.com</a>.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nThanks, and of best of effort to you in sorting through what is likely to be<br>\r\na large quantity of excellent entries. If you need any more information from<br>\r\nme, please let me know.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nVictor David Sandiego<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<a href="mailto:99Poets@VictorDavid.com">99Poets@VictorDavid.com</a><br>\r\n<br>\r\n206.317.1345 (U.S. Skype #)<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nManuscript: The First Book of Muwadi<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nAttachments:<br>\r\n<br>\r\nC&amp;R_Press-The First Book of Muwadi-Victor David Sandiego-Manuscript.pdf<br>\r\n<br>\r\nC&amp;R_Press-The First Book of Muwadi-Victor David Sandiego-CoverLetter.pdf<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\nPayPal transaction number: 1XY62010HC523101P<br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\n <br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</blockquote></span></body></html>');
