:Ignore''>·<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>How the world ends when I leave the metro<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoListParagraph style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol;color:#002060''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>·<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>Must climb his neck<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoListParagraph style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol;color:#002060''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>·<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>The headlong echo of your sorrow<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoListParagraph style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol;color:#002060''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>·<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>The one act play of man<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoListParagraph style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol;color:#002060''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>·<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>The radio plays Bruce Springsteen<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoListParagraph style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol;color:#002060''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>·<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>The rattle of my song<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoListParagraph style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol;color:#002060''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>·<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>Winter quarters<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>As requested, a brief bio:<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal>Victor David Sandiego lives in the high desert of central México where he walks the cities, plays drums with jazz combos and in musical / poetry collaborations, writes, and studies. His work appears in various journals and on public radio and he has won a few contests.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>Thanks for considering these. Please let me know if you need more information.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>Victor David<o:p></o:p></span></p></div></body></html>');
