xt-decoration:underline;}\r\nspan.Heading2Char\r\n\t{mso-style-name:"Heading 2 Char";\r\n\tmso-style-link:"Heading 2";\r\n\tfont-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";\r\n\tfont-weight:bold;}\r\nspan.SubtitleChar\r\n\t{mso-style-name:"Subtitle Char";\r\n\tmso-style-priority:11;\r\n\tmso-style-link:Subtitle;\r\n\tfont-family:"Verdana","sans-serif";\r\n\tletter-spacing:.6pt;}\r\nspan.EmailStyle20\r\n\t{mso-style-type:personal-compose;\r\n\tfont-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";\r\n\tcolor:#002060;}\r\n.MsoChpDefault\r\n\t{mso-style-type:export-only;\r\n\tfont-size:10.0pt;\r\n\tfont-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";}\r\n@page WordSection1\r\n\t{size:8.5in 11.0in;\r\n\tmargin:1.0in 1.0in 1.0in 1.0in;}\r\ndiv.WordSection1\r\n\t{page:WordSection1;}\r\n--></style><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<o:shapedefaults v:ext="edit" spidmax="1026" />\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<o:shapelayout v:ext="edit">\r\n<o:idmap v:ext="edit" data="1" />\r\n</o:shapelayout></xml><![endif]--></head><body lang=EN-US link=blue vlink=purple><div class=WordSection1><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>Hello Popshot &#8211;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>I&#8217;ve included 3 poems in this email that are related to your theme of Birth. At least loosely. As for a little bit about myself: Eclectic but I gravitate toward the mystical, mythological, and surreal. Someone said: philosophical music of dreams. Been published in the United States. Won a couple prizes. I live mostly in Mexico where I spend time walking the cities, drinking coffee, hanging out with life, writing. I love Cuban,&nbsp; reggae and jazz music, and I play the drums. Lots of fun! Like most all creatures except flies and mosquitos. Haven&#8217;t been in jail for a long time.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>Okay, here are the poems. Thanks for considering these.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''>Victor David<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><h2><a name="_GoBack"></a>No army can withstand the strength of an idea whose time has come<o:p></o:p></h2><p class=MsoSubtitle><i>- Victor Hugo<o:p></o:p></i></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal>Okay, you throw your hymns at God and in the confessional<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>stifle your doubt.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Your new forged face is on holy fire and you won<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>a brand new passion covered in bliss.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>An eccentric outing old friend but think &#8211; about your mum<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>and the calendars<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>she crosses off when doctor rings his news<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>in measured hammer blows.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Look, the illusion shows. Come to the edge of the music<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>and listen to your mind<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>stumble<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>down scales like drunken jazz notes.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Have to say though, nothing breaks your stubborn spirit<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>with bats or bricks.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Nothing shatters your prayer, even death<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>runs away from you now.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>But please look at us. We cannot hope to understand<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>how you fell from this new birth canal<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>or the exact depth<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>of your attachment to this latest life.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><h2>Out of whom came seven devils<o:p></o:p></h2><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>His head is mushier than I remember<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>and if this is my brother<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>converted by a roadside bomb to your Jesus, it just won&#8217;t do<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>because we are still <i>civilized</i>; we have institutions.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>We have records of who was covered in placenta<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>from the heartland<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>before law slithered into gloves<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>to wrench the forceps from the womb<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>and we know exactly which constitutional sons<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>confronted the prospect<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>of death by scrap iron bits and bolts<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>and who favored instead to risk their elections<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>on this new idea of endless turbulent bluster,<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>to pull it from between the legs<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>of that woman not yet cured of evil spirits<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>and slap it screaming in the morning with judges.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:#002060''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><h2>Today he is older than dirt<o:p></o:p></h2><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt''>from: <i>The First Book of Muwadi</i><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Morning is a half-eaten apple at the gate.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>No one owns a hammer these days; only sticks beat the bars now<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>that you share your lips and throat with the crowd.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>History will never repeal this moment; here we lash our daughters <o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>to Guadalupe &#8211; to the sound of the deer skin drum.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Beyond the next hilltop is blindness, madness<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>never spent the night here, never knocked the door<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>aside with calloused hands to lead Grandfather into the desert.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>When we die, the body inherits dust<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>and staggers to the grave on hesitant limbs.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>But for your sake, we keep our grievances private<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>sum our sweat in silence on the kneeling pad<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>or stumble but a vowel or two over our tone-deaf tongue.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>For this day marks the birth of our headstrong ways with you;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>it spills out of golden cups<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>that march over the tallest cedar we can see<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>fills our lungs with delirium and honey<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>in the knowledge<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>that you will live<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>beyond our longest lifetime.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p></div></body></html>');
