y collaborations, writes, and studies. His work appears in various journals and on public radio. His web site is victordavid.com.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Thank you. I&#8217;m glad to have an opportunity to send these your way. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Sincerely,<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Victor David Sandiego<o:p></o:p></p></div></body></html>');
INSERT INTO "submission_message" ("id", "entry_id", "submissionbatchid", "outgoing", "sender_name", "sender_email", "recipient_name", "recipient_email", "subject", "display", "sent_date", "received_date", "body_format", "body") VALUES (135, E'00000000FC0A50B868F35745AE9D2EED70629592A4022000', 182, E'1', E'Victor David Sandiego', E'99poets@victordavidsandiego.com', E'''lareview.poetry@gmail.com''', E'lareview.poetry@gmail.com', E'Poetry Submission - LA Review', E'Poetry Submission - LA Review', '2010-09-29 04:23:56', '2010-09-29 04:23:00', 1, E'Dear LA Review -\r\n\r\nThird time may be a leprechaun. Or maybe you don''t live in magic. The following titles are attached:\r\n\r\n-- I cannot be respectable without it\r\n-- The elephant death of war\r\n\r\nAs requested, a brief bio:\r\n----\r\nVictor David Sandiego divides his time between México and the United States. David was the winner of the 1st WordStorm Poetry Competition held on Vancouver Island in British Columbia and the winner of the 2009 Crab Creek Review poetry contest. His work has appeared (or will appear) in Floating Bridge Review, Crab Creek Review, Cascade, Grasslimb, Cerise Press, and on public radio. He performs with a musical / poetry collaborative group, Band of Poets. His website is www.VictorDavid.com\r\n----\r\n\r\nPlease let me know if you need any more swelter. Thank you.\r\n\r\nVictor David Sandiego\r\n\r\nwww.VictorDavidSandiego.com');
INSERT INTO "submission_message" ("id", "entry_id", "submissionbatchid", "outgoing", "sender_name", "sender_email", "recipient_name", "recipient_email", "subject", "display", "sent_date", "received_date", "body_format", "body") VALUES (136, E'00000000FC0A50B868F35745AE9D2EED7062959284032000', 171, E'1', E'Victor David Sandiego', E'poetry2009@victordavidsandiego.com', E'''lareview.poetry@gmail.com''', E'lareview.poetry@gmail.com', E'Poetry submission (4 poems) - LA Review', E'Poetry submission (4 poems) - LA Review', '2010-05-13 10:49:40', '2010-05-13 10:49:00', 1, E'Dear LA Review -\r\n\r\nThank you for an opportunity to submit a few poems for your consideration. The following titles are attached:\r\n\r\nBreaking bread with Muwadi\r\nPROMISES\r\nEl antílope y el oso\r\nThe journey to Saint Francis\r\n\r\nAs requested, a brief bio:\r\n\r\nVictor David Sandiego divides his time between México and the United States. David was the winner of the 1st WordStorm Poetry Competition held on Vancouver Island in British Columbia and the winner of the 2009 Crab Creek Review poetry contest. His work has appeared (or will appear) in Floating Bridge Review, Crab Creek Review, Cascade, Grasslimb, Cerise Press, and on public radio. He performs with a musical / poetry collaborative group, Band of Poets. His website is www.victordavidsandiego.com.\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks again. Please let me know if you need any more information.\r\n\r\nVictor David Sandiego');
