<li class=MsoNormal style=''mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1''>Sanctuary<o:p></o:p></li><li class=MsoNormal style=''mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1''>The Second Death Of God<o:p></o:p></li><li class=MsoNormal style=''mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1''>Weightlessness<o:p></o:p></li></ul><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>With respect to your guidelines, none of these pieces are currently under consideration elsewhere.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>As requested, a brief bio:<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=Indentedjustified>Victor David Sandiego lives in the high desert of central México where he walks the cities and mountains, plays drums with jazz combos and in musical / poetry collaborations, writes, and studies. His work appears in various journals and on public radio. His web site is victordavid.com.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Thank you. Please let me know if you need more information.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Victor David Sandiego<span style=''font-family:"Tahoma","sans-serif";color:black''><o:p></o:p></span></p></div></body></html>');
