="edit" data="1" />\r\n</o:shapelayout></xml><![endif]--></head><body lang=EN-US link=blue vlink=purple><div class=WordSection1><p class=MsoNormal>December 15, 2013<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Dear Editors of The Lindenwood Review &#8211;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>I&#8217;m running a bit late but on this last day of your submission period for 2013, I&#8217;d like to share the following pieces for your consideration:<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>·<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif"''>Scapegoat<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>·<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif"''>Painting<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>·<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif"''>Somewhere in New Orleans<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>·<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif"''>The Second Death Of God<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoListParagraphCxSpLast style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo2''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>·<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif"''>To My Old Friend<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>As requested, a brief bio:<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=Indented><span style=''font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif"''>Victor David Sandiego lives in the high desert of central México where he writes, studies, and plays drums with jazz combos and in musical / poetry collaborations. His work appears&nbsp; in various journals (Cerise Press, Crab Creek Review, Floating Bridge Review, Off The Coast, Generations Literary Journal, Poetry Salzburg Review, others) and has been featured on public radio. He is the founder and current editor of Subprimal Poetry Art. His website is victordavid.com.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Thanks much for taking a look. I appreciate the opportunity to share these with you. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Sincerely,<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Victor David Sandiego<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''font-size:10.0pt;color:black''>attached: &nbsp;The Lindenwood Review_2013-12-15-15-00-51-010.docx<o:p></o:p></span></p></div></body></html>');
