t:-.25in;\r\n\tfont-family:"Courier New";}\r\n@list l0:level6\r\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\r\n\tmso-level-text:\\F0A7;\r\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:none;\r\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\r\n\ttext-indent:-.25in;\r\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\r\n@list l0:level7\r\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\r\n\tmso-level-text:\\F0B7;\r\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:none;\r\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\r\n\ttext-indent:-.25in;\r\n\tfont-family:Symbol;}\r\n@list l0:level8\r\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\r\n\tmso-level-text:o;\r\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:none;\r\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\r\n\ttext-indent:-.25in;\r\n\tfont-family:"Courier New";}\r\n@list l0:level9\r\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\r\n\tmso-level-text:\\F0A7;\r\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:none;\r\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\r\n\ttext-indent:-.25in;\r\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\r\nol\r\n\t{margin-bottom:0in;}\r\nul\r\n\t{margin-bottom:0in;}\r\n--></style><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<o:shapedefaults v:ext="edit" spidmax="1026" />\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<o:shapelayout v:ext="edit">\r\n<o:idmap v:ext="edit" data="1" />\r\n</o:shapelayout></xml><![endif]--></head><body lang=EN-US link=blue vlink=purple><div class=WordSection1><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black''>Dear Gemini &#8211;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black''>I&#8217;ve included the following 3 pieces for the Gemini Magazine Poetry Open.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoListParagraph style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol;color:black''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>&middot;<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''color:black''>The Second Death Of God<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoListParagraph style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol;color:black''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>&middot;<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''color:black''>They Still Take Their Own Low Road<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoListParagraph style=''text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1''><![if !supportLists]><span style=''font-family:Symbol;color:black''><span style=''mso-list:Ignore''>&middot;<span style=''font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"''>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><![endif]><span style=''color:black''>Ambitions Of Dreams<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black''>Thank you.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black''>Victor David Sandiego <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black''>99Poets@VictorDavid.com<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black''>Pay Pal Amount: $5.00<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black;background:white''>Pay Pal Confirmation number: 2C05297629849402F<o:p></o:p></span></p><div style=''border:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in''><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black;background:white''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p></div><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black;background:white''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><h2><a name="_GoBack"></a>They Still Take Their Own Low Road<o:p></o:p></h2><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>In a loosely woven moonlight circling<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>an embryonic Earth, we drool<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>a horde of original infants from our teeth<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>into the soft hands of the leather hills.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>These flawless bodies, our impeccable children<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>suffer only birth,<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>for we, creators of all human hardship, shield<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>them with our stubborn affection.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Now they grow! Our beautiful offspring<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>exquisitely carved of wild limbs, free<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>to expel the dead animals from their blood. A she-wolf<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>licks her cubs as do we, descended from a cruel fever<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>dribble upon our precious children<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>all the fluid history of our race.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Yet they howl so soon<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>with joyous October death, our children<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>on their own low road<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>while the elder we<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>in our unnerving endless nights<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>gently brush the blindness<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>from their immaculate infant eyes.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><h2>The Second Death Of God<o:p></o:p></h2><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=''text-align:justify''>And so he comes (as he knew someday he must) to despise the tsunami of thoughts and stories that wash over him, drowning him in an incessant procession of celestial bodies, forests, street cafes, beggar faces, oceans and ships. Each rock he harbors, rising as they do above the tideline of voices, touches his silence only briefly before he sweeps once more into the magnificent phosphorescent churning of creation.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=''text-align:justify''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal style=''text-align:justify''>A man hates what he needs because it binds him to his unspoken desires, and imprisons him deep inside his life. He considers using the knife to slice an arterial to God but he has a deep fear of blindness. The colossal weight of the sky could crush his vision to lavender pulp and he isn&#8217;t ready to leave the world of ferns, footprints and pine needles behind.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><h2>Ambitions Of Dreams<o:p></o:p></h2><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>In dreams, desire<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>screams its loudest of birds, and dreams<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>are woven<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>with threads of ruin and rebirth<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>as they shout declarations<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>to a world<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>of cancer and love<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>that they live!<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>that they shovel the senseless<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>into the garden shadows<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>where skins<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>of old dogmas are buried<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>and from this pronouncement of lust<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>this nomadic testimony of life<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>that moves with slow horses<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>across the desert<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>rises a state of grace<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>like smoke<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>from a distant leg of roasting meat.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal><span style=''color:black''><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p></div></body></html>');
