ot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">From:</span></b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Tahoma&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"> <a href="mailto:dirtychaimag=gmail.com@email.submittable.com">dirtychaimag=gmail.com@email.submittable.com</a> [<a href="mailto:dirtychaimag=gmail.com@email.submittable.com">mailto:dirtychaimag=gmail.com@email.submittable.com</a>] <b>On Behalf Of </b>Dirty Chai<br><b>Sent:</b> Monday, January 20, 2014 12:03 PM<br><b>To:</b> Victor David Sandiego<br><b>Subject:</b> RE: [Dirty Chai] Metropolis of Crooked Tracks<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt">Dear Victor David Sandiego, <br><br>Thank you so much for allowing Dirty Chai to read your work! <br><br>We love AT THE GATE OF MUWADI and FOR THE LOVE OF THESE CREEDS and would be honored to feature them in our e-publication, Dirty Chai: Issue Two: Adventureland. Your piece will also appear on <a href="http://www.dirtychaimag.com">http://www.dirtychaimag.com</a> as part of our online literary content following the publication of the issue. <br><br>Below you will find a link to the Author’s Agreement. Please submit the form at your earliest convenience. Once received, we will prepare your work for publication. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us. <br><br>Note: your work will not be published without a completed Author''s Agreement. <br><br>Thank you again. <br><br>Sincerely, <br>Azia DuPont <br>Founder &amp; Co. Editor, Dirty Chai <br><br>Link to Author Agreement: <br><a href="http://bit.ly/1gAv2bS">http://bit.ly/1gAv2bS</a> <o:p></o:p></p></div></div></blockquote></body></html>');
