e it in our upcoming issue-- but only if you feel comfortable with our terms. Your happiness is most important and I, on behalf of Dirty Chai, respect any decision you come to.<o:p></o:p></p></div><div><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p></div><div><p class="MsoNormal">If you have any other questions or concerns, please do not hesitate to shoot me another email.<o:p></o:p></p></div><div><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p></div><div><p class="MsoNormal">-Azia DuPont<o:p></o:p></p></div><div><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p></div><div><p class="MsoNormal"><br>Sent from my iPhone<o:p></o:p></p></div><div><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt"><br>On Jan 20, 2014, at 7:09 PM, "Victor David Sandiego" &lt;<a href="mailto:99poets@victordavid.com">99poets@victordavid.com</a>&gt; wrote:<o:p></o:p></p></div><blockquote style="margin-top:5.0pt;margin-bottom:5.0pt"><div><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">Hello Azia DuPont</span><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">Thank you for your note. That’s great that you want publish the two pieces.</span><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">I’ve read the Author’s Agreement and am not comfortable with the part titled “Changes To Work”.&nbsp; I can understand that at times an editor wants changes and that publication is contingent upon the author agreeing to those changes. But I’m not willing to agree to the possibility of changes to title and/or text without my approval. Formatting changes I can understand to fit web pages or a particular book size, but this section goes beyond that. </span><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">If you can assure me that in this case there won’t be any alterations to the titles or texts or the two pieces, I can proceed. Thanks for your understanding and for selecting my work for Dirty Chai.</span><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">Sincerely</span><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family:&quot;Cambria&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;">Victor David</span><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#1F497D">&nbsp;</span><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Tahoma&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">From:</span></b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Tahoma&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;"> <a href="mailto:dirtychaimag=gmail.com@email.submittable.com">dirtychaimag=gmail.com@email.submittable.com</a> [<a href="mailto:dirtychaimag=gmail.com@email.submittable.com">mailto:dirtychaimag=gmail.com@email.submittable.com</a>] <b>On Behalf Of </b>Dirty Chai<br><b>Sent:</b> Monday, January 20, 2014 12:03 PM<br><b>To:</b> Victor David Sandiego<br><b>Subject:</b> RE: [Dirty Chai] Metropolis of Crooked Tracks</span><o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt">Dear Victor David Sandiego, <br><br>Thank you so much for allowing Dirty Chai to read your work! <br><br>We love AT THE GATE OF MUWADI and FOR THE LOVE OF THESE CREEDS and would be honored to feature them in our e-publication, Dirty Chai: Issue Two: Adventureland. Your piece will also appear on <a href="http://www.dirtychaimag.com">http://www.dirtychaimag.com</a> as part of our online literary content following the publication of the issue. <br><br>Below you will find a link to the Author’s Agreement. Please submit the form at your earliest convenience. Once received, we will prepare your work for publication. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us. <br><br>Note: your work will not be published without a completed Author''s Agreement. <br><br>Thank you again. <br><br>Sincerely, <br>Azia DuPont <br>Founder &amp; Co. Editor, Dirty Chai <br><br>Link to Author Agreement: <br><a href="http://bit.ly/1gAv2bS">http://bit.ly/1gAv2bS</a> <o:p></o:p></p></div></blockquote></div></div></blockquote></body></html>');
