rial Rights, the author may<br>not allow this piece to be published or displayed elsewhere in English<br>until Stone Telling has published it. As a part of this agreement, the<br>Author grants us ongoing non-exclusive rights to display the poem(s)<br>in our on-line archive. The author is also granting Stone Telling<br>non-exclusive rights to include the author’s poem(s) in any e-book<br>editions of Stone Telling. In addition, the author is granting<br>non-exclusive print anthology rights for possible inclusion of the<br>Author’s poem(s) in a print anthology. In addition, the Author is<br>granting Stone Telling promotional rights to publish, promote, and<br>market materials making use of the poem(s), and to license others to<br>do so.<br><br>All future publications of the above named poem(s) should be<br>accompanied by the following printed notice: “First appeared in Stone<br>Telling.”<br>The publishers of Stone Telling reserve the right to assign<br>art/illustrations to any poem at their discretion. Any rights not<br>specifically granted hereunder are reserved by the author.<br>Upon publication, all rights revert to the author.<br><br>Some additional information we''ll need before publication:<br>&nbsp;<br>1. An updated bio of 100 words or less, in third person.<br><br>2.Payment information - whether you would like to be paid by check or<br>by paypal, and to what address the payment should be sent.<br><br>3. Optional: an mp3 recording of the poem. We would love to receive it<br>within the next two weeks, but longer is a possibility.<br><br>Thank you and all the best,<br><br>Bogi, Shweta and Rose.<o:p></o:p></p></div><div><p class=MsoNormal><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><div><p class=MsoNormal>On Sun, Aug 30, 2015 at 3:45 PM, Victor D. Sandiego &lt;<a href="mailto:99poets@victordavid.com" target="_blank">99poets@victordavid.com</a>&gt; wrote:<o:p></o:p></p><p class=MsoNormal>Dear Rose and Shweta -<br><br>Thank you very much. I''m glad that you liked the pieces; no worries on 